doc.after: Potamon fluviatile has a generalist diet feeding on vegetable debris scraping algae from surfaces or preying on frogs tadpoles and various invertebrates such as insect larvae snails or worms No predator seems to specialise on P fluviatile but a number of animals take it opportunistically including rats foxes weasels birds of prey and jays The most significant predator may be mankind with individual prospectors able to catch 3 000 to 10 000 in one season
